Catalyze - Class in io.catalyze.sdk.android
Base class for making Catalyze.io API calls.
CatalyzeError - Class in io.catalyze.sdk.android
On an API call failure the Catalyze API will return one or more error entries.
CatalyzeException - Exception in io.catalyze.sdk.android
CatalyzeException will be returned to the onError method of the user callback handler if an error is encountered during a Catalyze API call.
CatalyzeListener<T> - Class in io.catalyze.sdk.android
Response handler for Catalyze API calls.
CatalyzeListener(Context) - Constructor for class io.catalyze.sdk.android.CatalyzeListener
The listener must be provided with a context to execute under (this is used beneath the Catalyze SDK by Volley).
CatalyzeObject - Class in io.catalyze.sdk.android
Base class for different Catalyze objects
CatalyzeRequest<T> - Class in io.catalyze.sdk.android
This class handles all Catalyze JSON network requests.
CatalyzeRequest(int, JSONArray, String, Response.Listener<T>, Response.ErrorListener) - Constructor for class io.catalyze.sdk.android.CatalyzeRequest
Make a request where the content is a JSON array.
CatalyzeRequest(int, String, JSONObject, Response.Listener<T>, Response.ErrorListener) - Constructor for class io.catalyze.sdk.android.CatalyzeRequest

CatalyzeUser - Class in io.catalyze.sdk.android
This class is a critical element to understand when interacting with the SDK (and thus the Catalyze API).
codeLookup(String, String, CatalyzeListener<UmlsResult[]>) - Method in class io.catalyze.sdk.android.UMLS

compareTo(CatalyzeUser) - Method in class io.catalyze.sdk.android.CatalyzeUser
